  <tr class="darktable"><td>
  <h3><a name="attach">Can I attach a file to my post?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  No.  File attachment has been turned off for these boards.
  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="login">How do I login?!?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  <br>If you have registered an account (username) within our forums, you must login in order to take advantage of all of the features. To login, look in the upper right hand corner of your screen for the "Login" link. This link will take you to a page that allows for you to enter your Username and Password. Keep in mind that the Password is always case sensitive. This means that the letters "S" and "s" are considered different by the software.
 
  <p>Once you have entered your Username and Password, you'll be brought to what is called the "Start Page". This start page allows for you to see if you have any "Private" messages. Once here, you can enter the main forum area by clicking on the "Main Index" link at the top of the page. This will list out the forums for you.


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="profile">How do I edit my Profile?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  <p>Take advantage of the versatility of our forums. You can choose between different styles and views in your own custom profile. All you need to do is edit your profile, to do this, follow the instructions outlined below:

  <p>1.) Click on the <b>Edit Profile</b> option at the top of the Forums.<br>
  <p>2.) Next, Click on the <b>Display Preferences</b> option.

  <p>Your will see a number of options available to you. Depending on the options you choose, you can fully customize the look and feel of the forums. Here are a couple of examples.

  <p>For those who prefer the look and feel of the Ultimate Bulletin Board (UBB), choose:</p>

  <p>Sort: <b>Descending Date</b><br>
  Mode: <b>Flat Mode</b><br>
  View: <b>Collapsed View</b><br>
  Post Format: <b>Side</b><br>

  <p>If you prefer the threaded style of the WWWBoards, choose:</p>

  <p>Sort: <b>Descending Date</b><br>
  Mode: <b>Threaded Mode</b><br>
  View: <b>Expanded View</b><br>
  Post Format: <b>Top</b><br>

  <p>Once these settings are saved, they become your default settings. You may edit these preferences anytime.</p>


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="sortorder">Why are Subject, Poster and Posted On clickable?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  You can click on any of these to change the order in which the posts are sorted and displayed.  If you click on Subject once, it will display posts by Subject in reverse alphabetical order.  If you click on it again it will display posts by Subject in alphabetical order.  Poster and Posted on works similarly.


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="email">Why do you ask for a two email addresses?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  The real email address is used for email notifications and forum subscriptions and to email your password.  The other is what other users see when they view your profile.  We realize that some people don't want everyone to know their normal email address, but we need to know it in case you want to subscribe to a forum or if you want to have replies emailed to you.  For this reason you can give us your real email address that only we will see and you can provide a different one for the general public.  Some people like to put in something like scream@no.spam.wwwthreads.com.  This way people can still figure out what your real email address is, but spamming agents can't just parse through the page and spam you.

  
  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="register">Why should I register a Username?</a></h3>
<p>
</td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  By registering a Username, you will be able to edit your profile and preferences.  You will get the most out of your time here if you change your profile to suit your individual tastes.  There are alot of options in your profile to make your experience here more enjoyable, so please take a few moments to try the various settings.  Also only people with registered Usernames can take advantage of the "New Posts" feature upon each visit.  
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="html">Can I use HTML in my posts?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
<p>There are 2 ways that this can be configured on a per board basis. If HTML 
  is On then you will see <b>HTML is On</b> and you can use normal HTML in your 
  posts. If Markup is on you will see <b>Markup is On</b>. The following tags 
  are available for your use if Markup is enabled: </p>
<p><b>General Markup</b></p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="darktable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[b]</b> </font> Text <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/b]</b></font></td>
    <td class="darktable">Makes the given text <b>bold</b>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="lighttable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[email]</b> </font> joe@blow.com <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/email]</b></font><br>
      <font class="standouttext"> </font></td>
    <td class="lighttable">Makes the given email address clickable.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="darktable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[i]</b> </font> Text <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/i]</b></font><br>
      <font class="standouttext"> </font></td>
    <td class="darktable">Makes the given text <i>italic</i>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="lighttable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[center]</b> </font> Text <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/center]</b></font></td>
    <td class="lighttable">Centers the given text within the message.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="darktable"> <font class="standouttext"><b>[image] </b></font>URL<font class="standouttext"><b> [/image]</b></font> </td>
    <td class="darktable">Puts the given url in an img src tag.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="lighttable"><font class="standouttext"> <b>[pre]</b> </font> text <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/pre]</b></font><br>
    </td>
    <td class="lighttable">Surrounds the given text with pre tags. </td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="darktable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[quote]</b> </font> text <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/quote]</b></font></td>
    <td class="darktable">Surrounds the given text with blockquote and hr's. This markup tag is 
      used for quoting a reply.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="lighttable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[url]</b> </font> link <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/url]</b></font></td>
    <td class="lighttable">Makes the given url into a link.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="middle"> 
    <td width="220" class="darktable"><font class="standouttext"><b>[url=link]</b> </font> title <font class="standouttext"> 
      <b>[/url]</b></font></td>
    <td class="darktable">Makes the given title into a hyperlink pointing to link.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
