  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="help">I am having trouble logging in! Help!</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  <P>If you are having trouble logging into the forums please go through the following check list. You may find be able to resolve your problem this way.<BR>

  <P>1.) Make sure you are entering your password correctly. They are case-sensitive.<BR>
  2.) Ensure that your browser supports cookies and if so, check the security level you're using. High levels of security on some browsers will automatically reject cookies. In order to use the key features of the forums you'll need to accept cookies.<BR> 
  3.) Completely logout by hitting the logout link on the page, and then log back in again.<BR> 
  4.) After logging in, you may have to hit the reload/refresh button on your Web browser to expedite the authentication process.<BR> 
  5.) If you continue to have problems, go to the login page. Enter your Username in the Username field and then click on "I forgot my password." A temporary password will be generated and emailed to the email address used for the account specified. <b>Note: You MUST enter a Username in the Username field before you click on the "I forgot my password" button.</b>

  <p>If after all of this you still have trouble, feel free to contact me at <a href="mailto:Jhariden@Stratics.com?subject=Forum Help">Jhariden@Stratics.com</a>


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="titles">What are these Titles all about?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  <br>Everyone has a title within the forum. You will notice them below the Username in people's posts or also in the "Who's Online" area of the forums. It is very important to note that these titles truly hold no significant importance overall. They have only been added for fun and they are based on the number of posts that have been made by the user. The list below shows the Titles currently being used:
<pre>
0	Visitor
31	Adventurer
100	Journeyman
300	Seasoned Veteran
500	Sage
750	Lore Keeper
1000	Lore Master
1250	Slightly Crazed
1500	Certifiable
2000    Babbling Loonie
</pre>

  <br>There are some other titles that do hold more significance however. These are titles that we have provided for Game Developers and other important representatives from gaming companies. This is to ensure you that their titles are legitimate, as only Administrators have the authority to grant such titles.


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="cookies">Do I have to accept cookies?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  Yes.  Cookies are used to track your Username/Password and which posts you have read for your current session.  Without accepting cookies some functions won't work properly.


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="forgotpassword">I forgot my password!</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  <br>If you have forgotten your password, do not worry! You can very easily have a temporary password emailed to you automatically. All you need to do is go to the login page of the forum and enter your username in the username field. Then click on the button marked, “I forgot my password”. A temporary password will be sent to the email address of the username you entered in the username field.
     <p>This process is safe because the password is only mailed to the original owner of the account. There is no way anyone can obtain the password by using this feature.</p>

  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="changepassword">How do I change my password?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
<br>You may change your password anytime. All you need to do is click on the “Edit Profile” option found on nearly any page within our forums. Then click on the option, “Basic Profile”. When you enter the Basic Profile screen, you’ll see a long list of options available for you to customize. The very first two fields on the page have to do with your password. To change your password, all you need to do is enter a new password in both of these fields. There are two fields so to ensure you’ve typed in the new password correctly. Once you have entered in the new information, click on the “Submit” button to save the information.
<p>Note: Please keep in mind that passwords in our forums are case sensitive. This means that “password” and “PASSWORD” are considered different by the system.</p>

  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="addimage">How do I add an image to my message (or signature)?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
<br>In order to add an image to your message or your signature, you must have the image already available on the web. This means that the file must be accessible via the web. This can be on your own personal web page for example.
<p>Once the image is available on the web, all you need to do is use the following “Markup Tag” in your message:
<p>[image]http://www.url_to_image.com/image_name.gif[/image]
<p>For example:
<p>Say you have an image called cateye.gif and you wish to add it to your post. The file is located your own personal web page located at <http://www.mywebsite.com/pics/>”. Your image markup would look like this in your message when you type it in:
<p>[image]http://www.mywebsite.com/pics/cateye.gif[/image]
<p>You would also do the same for your signature. In your signature, you need to visit the Preferences page. All you need to do is click on the “Edit Profile” option found on nearly any page within our forums. Then click on the option, “Basic Profile”. When you enter the Basic Profile screen, you’ll see a long list of options available for you to customize. If you scroll down you’ll see the signature field. Enter the information you’d like to use here and your image markup goes here as well.
<p><b>Please Note: We ask that you keep images in your signature relatively small. By this we mean both in over image size (width and height) and also in file size. The larger the image dimensions and size the longer it takes for pages to load in our forums. Please note the following rule regarding signature sizes:
<p>Please adhere to the following restriction for images that are not directly related to the topic of the thread under discussion (i.e. Images used as signatures):<br><br>Maximum size of image file(s): 35k<br>Maximum height of image(s): 125 pixels<br>Maximum width of image(s): 600 pixels</b>
<p>We’d prefer to keep the forums loading quickly for everyone. Thank you.

  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">
  <h3><a name="moreposts">I want to see more (or less) posts per page.</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">
  You can change the number of posts to be displayed per page by editing your profile.  You can set this from anything between 1 and 99 posts per page.  When you first sign up this gets set to 30 posts per page.


  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
  </td></tr><tr><td class="darktable">

  <h3><a name="buttons">What's with all the buttons?</a></h3>
  <p>
  </td></tr><tr><td class="lighttable">

  The buttons are used for navigation and displaying posts.  Depending on the screen you are on they may serve different purposes.
  <p><b>When displaying a list of all threads:</b>
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/previous.gif"> and <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/next.gif" > buttons will take you to the previous or next page of posts. 
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/all.gif" > button will take you to the index of all available forums.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/newpost.gif" > button will let you make a new post on that board.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/expand.gif" > and <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/collapse.gif" > buttons will allow you to toggle between expanded and
  collapsed threads. Expanded threads will show the subject of all posts and replies in a threaded format. Collapsed threads will show the subject of the main post along with the number of replies to that post.
  <p><b>When viewing individual threads:</b>
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/previous.gif" > and <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/next.gif" > buttons will take you to the previous or next thread.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/all.gif" > button will take you back to the listing of all posts on that page.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/flat.gif" > button allows you to view the entire thread on one page if there are any replies to the original message.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/threaded.gif" > button allows you to view the current post with all other posts on that thread displayed below in a threaded format.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/reply.gif" > button allows you to reply to a post.
  <br>- The <img src="/shared/forum_images/ltblue/edit.gif" > button allows you to edit a post.

  <p>&nbsp;
  </td></tr><tr><td class="alternatetable">
